Program: Outlook
Title: Overcoming Political Divisions in Cyprus
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbrfr
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
Greek and Turkish Cypriots coming together to find a bone marrow donor for a Greek Cypriot boy. Also, writer Jill Robinson on losing her memory and not recognising her husband. A report on drug-use in Amsterdam. Finally, singer Harry Connick Jr talks about his life and career.